# 2026-02-25 09:06:22.661057
+We want a very clean, minimal Next.js App Router page that shows connection status.
+
+Create folder src/app/test-connections/ and file page.tsx inside it.
+
+The page should be client component ('use client').
+
+Goals / features:
+
+1. Big title "Waterfront – Connection & Environment Test"
+
+2. Four simple status cards (use Tailwind + basic divs):
+   - Environment: shows NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and length of NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
+   - Supabase: initializes client with createClient from @supabase/supabase-js
+     → tries supabase.from('_dummy').select('count(*)').maybeSingle() or auth.getSession()
+     → shows "Connected ✅" / "Error ❌" + error message
+   - MQTT: uses mqtt library → connect to MQTT_BROKER_URL
+     → shows Connected / Disconnected / Error + timestamp of last status change
+   - Vercel: shows process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ENV or VERCEL_URL if available
+
+3. Add loading state (use useState + useEffect)
+
+4. Add "Refresh Status" button
+
+5. Install needed packages if missing: @supabase/supabase-js mqtt
+
+6. Clean, commented code, TypeScript, async/await
+
+7. Keep it beginner readable – no shadcn yet, simple div + tailwind classes
+
+After creation show me the new test-connections/page.tsx file content.

